      "goal_id": 1,
      "goal": "A1 weakly authenticates A2 on ccn(A2,A1)",
      "status": "attack found",
      "confidence": 80,
      "justification": "Weak authentication (non-injective agreement) requires that when A1 completes, A2 must have previously sent the authenticated data. However, A3 simply forwards A2's message without binding it to a fresh session or verifying its origin. An attacker can replay a captured message from A2 to A3 to A1, causing A1 to believe A2 is freshly authenticating, even if A2 did not initiate this run. There is no mechanism to distinguish a fresh transmission from a replay, and A3 acts as an untrusted intermediary without adding any freshness.",
